The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Goa arrests
                                                                                                               Goa arrests
                            
	Panaji, Oct. 15 (PTI): Goa police today said they had arrested four persons in connection with 10 deaths over the past four days in capital Panaji.         
	Those arrested are said to have confessed to killing a family of four, including a 35-year-old woman who was sexually abused before being murdered.         
	The main motive behind the murders was to avenge the womans refusal to have sex with them (the suspects), deputy inspector-general of police Ravindra Yadav said.                                                                                                                                                                           
